						<summary>

						<p>At the entrance into the central shrine in the Rāmanāthasvāmin temple, left side.</p>						

						<p>Rājarāja II. Year 7+1: 1153-54 A.D.</p>						

						<p>For the reason stated above in No. 657 the king of this inscription also may be identified with Rājarāja II.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of a <hi rend="italic">gōmukha</hi> by one Śiṅgapperumāḷ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Tirunīṟṟuchchōḻa-Mūvēnda-vēḷāṉ to god Tāyilunallīśuramuḍaiyār.</p>						

						</summary>
